snippet: The cause of the accident was not immediately clear, though officials said the ferry had been traveling at over 10 miles per hour just before the crash.
abstract: Ferry bound from Atlantic Highlands, NJ, to Manhattan crashes into Pier 11, injuring scores of people; cause of accident is not immediately clear, though officials say ferry had been traveling well above the pace of its typical crawl into the dock.

byline.original: By MATT FLEGENHEIMER and COLIN MOYNIHAN
byline.contributor: Wendy Ruderman, Marc Santora and Tim Stelloh contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: The cause of the accident was not immediately clear, though officials said the ferry had been traveling at over 10 miles per hour just before the crash.
